			"body": "> The fix for the gap causes the modal to not resize\r\n\r\nThat's because the right fix is not being used. The KeyboardAvoidingView needs to remain enabled when the keyboard is showing. That's the whole point of a KeyboardAvoidingView.\r\n\r\nI don't know what the correct fix is, so can't provide guidance how to do it. But the result should be that the behaviour matches Joplin 3.5, which is that it should resize with and without the keyboard showing, but without an extra gap and without covering the status bar at the top.\r\n\r\nIf it is too difficult for you to solve, then it might be best to choose a different bug to fix.",
